race.description: The Pinnacles Carnival Noms Close 13th Oct Handicap
race.comment: ASPHALT (4) burst onto the scene last campaign, winning three on-end in good figures. They were all on wet tracks however, and he'll have to do it on top of the ground today. Hard to ignore the way in which he did it however, and he'll be hard to beat if he can pick up where he left off. HYMNS OF ELADDAIR (1) resumed in strong order when coming over the top to win by 0.3L after being slowly away. He'll be better for that performance and the rise in trip is no issue. Can go back-to-back. GREAT EMOTION (11) stuck on well over 1200m last start but was no match for the winner, beaten 2.8L. Now third-up and out to 1400m looks a good move. She did win over 1300m first-up in April, so if she can improve out in trip, she'll be right in the finish. CENTRE BOND (6) was no match for a dominant winner last start but he was best of the rest. Strong claims off his recent efforts. I'M CRAFTY (5) surprised first-up but can build on that performance.
